===Chart history===
''Grey's Anatomy: The Music Event'' d<U+00E9>buted at number 24 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], with 19,000 copies sold.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1661426/britney-spears-femme-fatale-number-one-billboard.jhtml|title=Britney Spears' Femme Fatale Debuts At #1 On Billboard|last=Kaufman|first=Gil|date=April 6, 2011|publisher=[[MTV]]|accessdate=April 7, 2011}}</ref> It reached number 2 on the U.S. Soundtracks chart, and was the number 5 [[Independent Albums|Independent Album]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/heatseekers-songs#/charts/soundtracks?chartDate=2011-04-16|title=Soundtracks: Week of April 16, 2011|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=April 8, 2011|format=Note: to access peak, click the white area around the song}}</ref> "The Story" entered the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] singles chart at number 69,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/news/katy-perry-s-e-t-widens-lead-atop-hot-100-1005114432.story#/news/katy-perry-s-e-t-widens-lead-atop-hot-100-1005114432.story|title=Katy Perry's 'E.T.' Widens Lead Atop Hot 100|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=April 6, 2011|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=April 7, 2011}}</ref> and the [[Canadian Hot 100]] at 72.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/album/soundtrack/grey-s-anatomy/733002#/charts/hot-100?chartDate=2011-04-16&begin=61&order=position|title=Hot 100: Week of April 16, 2011|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=April 8, 2011|format=Note: to access peak, click the white area around the song}}</ref>

